</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC5FFE9A5137BB694A30B74" box="[1050,1219,236,261]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" type="description">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC5FFE9A5137BB694A30B74" blockId="12.[1050,1219,236,261]" box="[1050,1219,236,261]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">(FIVE SPECIES)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC5FFE9A2327A4F95C1080C" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC5FFE9A2327A4F93A3086E" blockId="12.[827,1443,276,543]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A2327A4F93D20B5B" box="[827,946,277,298]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Oegopsid with buccal connectives attached to the dorsal margins of ventral arms; without photophores; funnel–mantle locking apparatus straight, reaching the anterior mantle margin; fins without anterior lobes, with anterior fin attachment to mantle rather than gladius; tentacles with numerous carpal suckers; mitochondrial gene 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A5DA7A9795600B93" box="[1235,1280,461,482]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">trnI</emphasis>
between 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A4647A9795C20B93" box="[1389,1442,461,482]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">trnR</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A2667AB193D20871" box="[879,946,491,512]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">
trnS 
<quantity id="154B9B72FFC5FFE9A2AC7AB193D20871" box="[933,946,491,512]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" unit="in" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</emphasis>
in the following sequence: 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A5FF7AB693DC086E" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">trnK trnR trnI trnS1 nad2</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC5FFE9A232791295C1080C" blockId="12.[827,1441,584,637]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A232791293D0082C" box="[827,944,584,605]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">Remarks:</emphasis>
The original sense of 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC5FFE9A5DE791295C1082F" authorityName="BERRY" authorityYear="1920" box="[1239,1441,584,606]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Architeuthoidea">Architeuthoidea</taxonomicName>
included only the family 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC5FFE9A55D793D95FB080C" authority="(Berry, 1920)" baseAuthorityName="Berry" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[1108,1435,615,637]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Architeuthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">
Architeuthidae (
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFC5FFE9A406793295F1080D" author="Berry SS" box="[1295,1425,615,637]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" pagination="141 - 169" refId="ref14237" refString="Berry SS. 1920. Light production in cephalopods, I. An introductory survey. Biological Bulletin 38: 141 - 169." type="journal article" year="1920">Berry, 1920</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
